Package: songsim
Title: Visualize a song lyrics with a similarity matrix, a method first suggested by Colin Morris
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Date: 2017-10-15
Authors@R: c(
	person("Giora", "Simchoni", email = "gsimchoni@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
	person("Colin", "Morris", , "colin.morris@gmail.com", "aut")
	)
Description: This package holds a single function to calculate and visualize a "songsim" similarity matrix
	where cell (i, j) is filled if word i in a song's lyrics is the same as word j. This method was first
	suggested by Colin Morris (see URLs)
URL: https://colinmorris.github.io/blog/weird-pop-songs, https://colinmorris.github.io/SongSim/, http://giorasimchoni.com/2017/10/16/2017-10-16-repeat-yourself-the-songsim-package/
Depends: R (>= 3.4.1)
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Imports: purrr,
	reshape2
Suggests: heatmaply
